<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Rules - OWCS Tipping</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/global.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/layout.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/components.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/interactive.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/match-cards.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/pages/rules.css">
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/header') %>

  <main class="page-shell">
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <h1>Rules</h1>
        <p>
          Please read these guidelines before participating. This platform is intended to be a fair,
          enjoyable, and community-focused OWCS tipping experience.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="page-content">
      <div class="container rules-layout">
        <div class="rules-card">
          <h2>1. General Participation</h2>
          <p>
            OWCS Tipping is an unofficial, community-run tipping platform. By using the site,
            you agree to participate in good faith and respect both the competition and other users.
          </p>
          <p>
            Users are expected to use the site responsibly, submit genuine tips, and avoid any
            behaviour that disrupts the experience for others.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rules-card">
          <h2>2. Fair Play</h2>
          <p>
            Fair play is a core expectation of this site. Users must not attempt to gain an unfair
            advantage through manipulation, abuse of bugs, automation, or any other dishonest means.
          </p>
          <ul class="rules-list">
            <li>Do not exploit errors or loopholes in the tipping system.</li>
            <li>Do not use bots, scripts, or automated tools to place or alter tips unfairly.</li>
            <li>Do not attempt to interfere with another user’s account, tips, or credits.</li>
            <li>Do not create misleading or fake activity to manipulate rankings.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="rules-card">
          <h2>3. No Cheating or Abuse</h2>
          <p>
            Any attempt to cheat the system may result in action being taken against your account.
            This includes, but is not limited to:
          </p>
          <ul class="rules-list">
            <li>Using multiple accounts to gain an advantage.</li>
            <li>Abusing test routes, admin tools, or unfinished site features.</li>
            <li>Manipulating credits or tipping data outside intended site behaviour.</li>
            <li>Knowingly taking advantage of bugs without reporting them.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Accounts found to be abusing the platform may have tips removed, credits adjusted,
            rankings reset, or access revoked.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rules-card">
          <h2>4. Tipping Rules</h2>
          <p>
            Tips must be placed before the relevant match begins. Once a match is locked or completed,
            tips for that match can no longer be changed.
          </p>
          <p>
            Odds and credit values shown on the site are part of the site’s internal tipping system only.
            They are not real currency and do not represent real-money gambling.
          </p>
          <ul class="rules-list">
            <li>Only valid submitted tips will count.</li>
            <li>A user may only have one active tip per match unless the system explicitly allows edits.</li>
            <li>Completed matches will be resolved based on the recorded result in the system.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="rules-card">
          <h2>5. Credits and Rankings</h2>
          <p>
            Credits are an in-site scoring and tipping resource only. They do not hold real-world value,
            cannot be withdrawn, and cannot be exchanged for money or prizes unless explicitly stated.
          </p>
          <p>
            Leaderboard positions are based on the platform’s recorded credits and results. If an error
            is discovered, credits or rankings may be corrected to preserve fairness.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rules-card">
          <h2>6. Account Responsibility</h2>
          <p>
            Users are responsible for maintaining the security of their own account details. Do not share
            your login information with others.
          </p>
          <p>
            If suspicious activity is detected, the site administrators may review or restrict access to
            protect the integrity of the platform.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rules-card">
          <h2>7. Admin Decisions</h2>
          <p>
            Site administrators may intervene where necessary to correct bugs, remove unfair advantages,
            resolve disputes, or protect the integrity of the tipping system.
          </p>
          <p>
            In situations not explicitly covered by these rules, admins may make reasonable decisions in
            the interest of fair play and site stability.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rules-card">
          <h2>8. Unofficial Platform Notice</h2>
          <p>
            This is an unofficial OWCS tipping platform and is not affiliated with or endorsed by the
            Overwatch Champions Series or Blizzard Entertainment.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>